Section 1: Q&A; Pairs

Example 1.1

User

What is GPT?
AI Response

GPT (Generative Pre-trained Transformer) is an autoregressive language model trained to predict the next
token. GPT-3 and GPT-4 are large-scale versions capable of diverse language tasks.

Example 1.2

User

What is word embedding?
AI Response

Word embeddings map words to dense vectors where similar words are nearby. Word2Vec, GloVe, and
FastText are popular methods, used as NLP model input features.

Example 1.3

User

What is dropout?
AI Response

Dropout randomly sets a fraction of neuron activations to zero during training, preventing co-adaptation of
neurons and reducing overfitting.

Example 1.4

User

What is K-means clustering?
AI Response

K-means partitions data into K clusters by iteratively assigning points to the nearest centroid and updating
centroids as the mean of assigned points, minimizing intra-cluster variance.

Example 1.5

User

What is a confusion matrix?
AI Response

A confusion matrix shows counts of true/false positives and negatives for a classifier, enabling computation of
accuracy, precision, recall, and F1 score.

Example 1.6

User

What is cross-validation?
AI Response

Cross-validation splits data into k folds, training on k-1 and validating on one, rotating until all folds serve as
validation. Results are averaged for robust performance estimation.

Example 1.7

User

What is data augmentation?
AI Response



Data augmentation artificially increases training data by applying transformations like rotation, cropping, and
flipping to existing samples, improving model generalization.

Example 1.8

User

What is a GAN?
AI Response

A Generative Adversarial Network pits a generator (creates fake data) against a discriminator (identifies
fakes), training each other until the generator produces realistic data.

Example 1.9

User

What is a hyperparameter?
AI Response

A hyperparameter is a configuration setting external to the model—like learning rate or batch size—set
before training and tuned using validation performance.

Example 1.10

User

What is the ROC curve?
AI Response

The ROC curve plots true positive rate vs false positive rate at various thresholds. AUC (Area Under Curve)
summarizes performance—a perfect model has AUC = 1.0.



